issue.body:
When trying to bind the following json: `{"min":10,"max":"xxx"}`

to this java class:

```
class Range {
Double min;
Double max;
}
```

jackson throws an InvalidFormatException exception:
`Can not construct instance of java.lang.Double from String value 'xxx': not a valid Double value at [Source: {"min":10,"max":"xxx"}; line: 1, column: 10]`

Column 10 stops at: `{"min":10`, whearas we expect column 22: `{"min":10,"max":"xxx"`

**Proposed fix:**

Looking at the static `from` method from class InvalidFormatException:

```
        return new InvalidFormatException(msg, jp.getTokenLocation(),
                value, targetType);
```

I think it should be:

```
        return new InvalidFormatException(msg, jp.getCurrentLocation(),
                value, targetType);
```
